iolet Twilight to guide nightwalkers through the blinding light of day.<br>
<br>
The Code.<br>
<br>
Necropotence.  Above all, know you serve the Dead, and under the crimson moon no living soul can stand against you, Necromancer.<br>
<br>
Vengeance.  Your designs are your own, Necromancer, so long as they further the rising dark in which you exist and serve.  Interference must be punished, but mind that you know what is interference and what is aid.<br>
<br>
Alliance.  Your loyalty is to the Dead, to the howling of the wolves and the glory of the night, but an alliance you forge with the living is an alliance you must keep.  You are not invincible, Necromancer.<br>
<br>
Destruction.  While it is the nature of some to protect the living, it is your duty to draw down the stars upon those who wish you harm.  Remember, Necromancer - the fatal touch you give can also return to grapple with you.<br>
<br>
Courage.  You have nothing to fear, Necromancer.  You have tasted both the heat of living and the chill of the grave - the tangled road is known to you.  Never fear to take it, even if it means your death, for unlike all mankind, you can walk the road of Destruction and return home afterwards.<br>
<br>
Faith.  When the mortals who walk this land look upon your blighted robes and spit upon you, when the clerics of Tunare raise their holy symbols against you, when the light screams from the sky like arrows for your heart, have faith that their spit shall dry to dust, their hands shall one day fall to their sides without the strength to lift a brand against you, and that soon dusk shall fall.  You are a part of the balance between the brightness of the living and the quivering Veil which comes after.  Fear not, Necromancer.<br>
<br>
Prudence.  Never doubt your skills, Necromancer.  But know that you are yet mortal, though you are both living and unliving, and that always above you there is the Walker of the Violet Twilight, and it is She who guides your blade's stroke.  You are not the beginning and the end - know yourself.<br>
<br>
Reward.  In times of alliance, be gregarious. In times of solitude, gather your strength.  They amount to the same thing, in the end.  The Necromancer's allies make him great as he gives them strength.<br>
<br>
Beauty.  In life and death there is an unimaginable beauty which you can feel but never truly replicate, Necromancer.  As you strive to follow the Art, you must not forget the fragile taste of life even as you grow detached from it.  Nor can you dwell upon the dusty sweetness of what lies beyond the Veil while you live and breathe.  Two beauties, and neither can be experienced utterly - they can only be experienced fully.  There is a difference, I promise you.  Strive to experience both fully.<br>
<br>
Purpose.  For the sake of your mortal being, I shall hope you follow this benighted path not for the sake of gravebourne might, but because it is your path.  Hypocrisy is fatal.  Follow the path because you are made for it, and never for power.  For you cannot turn back now, Necromancer.<br>
<br>
Reservation.  Hold your thoughts to your breast, Necromancer, and keep them tightly held there.  They are yours to pursue as you wish and yours to solve to the limits of your knowledge.  It is not your place to grieve the world with your private concerns, as you alone may solve them.  And you strengthen with every move your mind makes to those ends.<br>
<br>
There are Heroes under every light, and under the sweet song of midnight.  I place the Code before you, Shadow's children.<br>
 <p>The Reaper with the Red Right Hand, <BR>--The Destain, Humwawa <BR>
Servant to the Walker of the Violet Twilight <BR>
